WEBVTT

00:01.129 --> 00:02.078
There are two kinds of folks

00:02.135 --> 00:03.735
who sit around thinking
about how to kill people:

00:04.069 --> 00:05.795
Psychopaths
and mystery writers.

00:06.033 --> 00:07.055
I'm the kind that pays better.

00:07.456 --> 00:08.055
Who am I?

00:08.145 --> 00:09.284
I'm Rick Castle.

00:09.285 --> 00:09.685
Castle.

00:09.719 --> 00:10.379
Castle.

00:10.380 --> 00:12.080
I really am ruggedly handsome,
aren't I?

00:12.134 --> 00:14.324
Every writer needs inspiration.
And I found mine.

00:14.534 --> 00:15.353
Detective Kate Beckett.

00:15.600 --> 00:16.867
Beckett.
Aah!

00:17.140 --> 00:19.225
Beckett?
Could you get some backup, please?

00:19.576 --> 00:21.460
<i>And thanks to my friendship</i>
<i>with the Mayor,</i>

00:21.511 --> 00:23.145
<i>I get to be on her case.</i>
Oh!

00:23.179 --> 00:25.748
Do I look like a killer to you?
Yes, you kill my patience.

00:25.782 --> 00:27.416
<i>And together,</i>
<i>we catch killers.</i>

00:27.964 --> 00:31.166
I hate this case.
I know. Isn't it great?

00:35.394 --> 00:37.729
Mom.

00:37.763 --> 00:40.966
Mom.

00:41.000 --> 00:43.735
Mom, are you here?

00:45.000 --> 00:51.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:59.685 --> 01:02.120
(Keypabeeping)

01:02.154 --> 01:04.089
Come on.

01:04.123 --> 01:06.191
Come on, mom. Answer.

01:06.225 --> 01:09.828
(Cell phone rings)

01:09.862 --> 01:13.798
(Ring)

01:13.833 --> 01:18.036
(Ring)

01:18.070 --> 01:20.205
(Ring)

01:20.239 --> 01:21.539
(Gasps)

01:21.574 --> 01:24.276
(Ring)

01:24.310 --> 01:26.945
(Grunts) Oh!

01:26.979 --> 01:29.281
Aah!

01:35.061 --> 01:36.628
(Martha) Oh, hello.

01:36.663 --> 01:39.031
Shouldn't you be
in school already?

01:39.065 --> 01:40.833
School doesn't start
for another hour.

01:40.915 --> 01:43.750
Yeah. If you were hoping to do the walk
of shame in private, you're outta luck.

01:43.833 --> 01:47.036
Oh, don't be silly. I just
didn't realize how early it was.

01:47.070 --> 01:50.205
I have been a bit distracted
this morning.

01:50.240 --> 01:52.841
Do you mean distracted,
or hypnotized by that giant rock

01:52.876 --> 01:54.443
on your finger?!
(Laughs)

01:55.416 --> 01:57.484
Wow.
Did Chet Palaburn propose?

01:57.518 --> 02:01.220
Uh, Alexis, I think it's about time
we start calling him Uncle Chet.

02:01.254 --> 02:03.256
Oh, now wait a minute.
Wait a minute, you two.

02:03.305 --> 02:04.640
I am not engaged, all right?

02:04.704 --> 02:06.972
Yes, Chet did propose
last night,

02:07.006 --> 02:09.241
and I told him, you know,
I needed time to think about it,

02:09.275 --> 02:12.110
and he insisted I keep the ring
while I make up my mind, so...

02:12.145 --> 02:13.545
Mm. Smart man.
Mm.

02:13.580 --> 02:15.747
Diamonds can be
very persuasive.

02:15.782 --> 02:18.684
I can hear it now, whispering...
(Whispers) "Keep me. Keep me."

02:18.718 --> 02:23.887
(Laughs) Unfortunately, now that
Chet has upped the ante,

02:23.919 --> 02:26.854
as they say,
I'm going to have to decide

02:26.889 --> 02:28.624
whether I'm in or I'm out.

02:28.659 --> 02:30.960
I thought you loved Chet.

02:30.995 --> 02:33.563
Oh, I do love him, darling.
I really do. I j--I...

02:33.597 --> 02:35.598
Well, you know, it's just
that for me, it's, uh--

02:35.633 --> 02:37.233
the thrill is gone.

02:37.268 --> 02:38.534
Yes,

02:38.569 --> 02:41.771
and it's been gone
for quite a while.

02:41.805 --> 02:43.606
Although this little fella
did bring it back

02:43.641 --> 02:45.575
for about ten minutes.
(Chuckles)
(Laughs)

02:45.609 --> 02:48.354
If he's not the one, then I
guess you shouldn't marry him.

02:48.364 --> 02:49.332
That's never stopped her before.

02:49.893 --> 02:52.094
And we miss having you here all the time.
Aw.

02:52.104 --> 02:54.171
Don't we, dad?

02:54.206 --> 02:56.374
(Martha and Alexis) Dad?
(Cell phone rings)

02:56.408 --> 02:58.175
Mm.
Saved by the Bell.

02:58.210 --> 02:59.277
(Beeps)

02:59.311 --> 03:01.946
Ah, it's Beckett.
Castle.

03:02.621 --> 03:04.288
Hey, did I hear you right?

03:04.323 --> 03:07.892
Our victim is Vivien Marchand,
the psychic medium?

03:07.926 --> 03:09.393
You've heard of her?

03:09.428 --> 03:11.796
Yeah. She was very popular
in certain Manhattan circles.

03:11.830 --> 03:14.198
Huh.
Matter of fact, she did a reading for me

03:14.233 --> 03:16.133
at a society party
about eight years ago.

03:16.168 --> 03:17.869
It was pretty extraordinary.

03:17.903 --> 03:19.203
"Extraordinary"?

03:19.238 --> 03:20.671
She got <i>everything</i> right.

03:20.706 --> 03:22.573
You know what?
Come to think of it,

03:22.608 --> 03:24.876
she told me
that a beautiful woman

03:24.910 --> 03:28.246
would one day move into my loft
and stay with me forever.

03:28.280 --> 03:31.182
She neglected to mention
it was my mother.

03:31.216 --> 03:33.751
(Ryan chuckles)
How did she die?

03:33.785 --> 03:36.220
Stabbed in the back of the neck
with an ice pick,

03:36.255 --> 03:39.956
and then stuffed into the sofa.
So she didn't see that coming.

03:40.322 --> 03:41.256
(Beckett)
When did she die?

03:41.293 --> 03:44.361
She's in full rigor.
I'd say yesterday afternoon

03:44.396 --> 03:46.730
is the approximate time of death.
(Esposito) I got a maintenance worker

03:46.765 --> 03:48.699
said he saw a man
leaving the back door

03:48.733 --> 03:51.702
of Vivien's office around 2:30
yesterday afternoon.
Description?

03:51.736 --> 03:53.971
Tall, Caucasian and tough looking.
All right, Ryan, check Vivien's calendar,

03:54.005 --> 03:55.940
and let's interview
her clients from yesterday.

03:55.974 --> 03:58.008
Maybe one of them
saw the guy.

03:58.043 --> 04:00.611
What I don't get is,
why put her in the couch?

04:00.645 --> 04:02.513
(Lanie) She was alive
when she went in.

04:02.597 --> 04:04.765
These scratches on her face
indicate that she tried to move.

04:06.025 --> 04:09.027
I'm gonna get her
back the lab.

04:09.061 --> 04:11.229
She's got a notation here
for 3:00 P.M. yesterday.

04:11.264 --> 04:13.665
It just says "T.J."

04:13.699 --> 04:15.267
And nothing else?

04:15.301 --> 04:17.336
Nope. Maybe T.J. was a ghost
coming to visit.

04:17.420 --> 04:19.498
Mediums are the ones that can
see ghosts, right, castle?

04:19.507 --> 04:20.684
Yes, psychics can tell the future.

04:21.194 --> 04:23.529
Mediums can tell the future
and talk to the dead.

04:23.612 --> 04:25.747
That's like saying
that psychics are con artists,

04:25.781 --> 04:27.749
and mediums are con artists
and charlatans.

04:28.814 --> 04:30.148
I mean, in the end,
they're all just fakes.

04:30.226 --> 04:32.494
You sound pretty certain
of yourself.

04:32.528 --> 04:33.963
That's because
when I started as a cop,

04:34.002 --> 04:37.104
I wasted a lot of time on
clairvoyants calling tip lines

04:37.139 --> 04:39.840
with information
that <i>never</i> led to anything.

04:40.512 --> 04:41.980
I mean, I'm surprised
you're so gullible.

04:41.988 --> 04:43.522
I'm not saying
I can speak with the dead.

04:43.609 --> 04:46.277
I'm just willing to admit that
there are people in this world

04:46.312 --> 04:49.514
who are more sensitive than me.
Now that's not hard to believe.

04:51.134 --> 04:53.469
Walked right into that one.
Mm-hmm.

04:53.503 --> 04:54.804
(Beckett) Ms. Marchand,
do you know of anyone

04:54.887 --> 04:56.989
that might have wanted
to harm your mother?

04:57.023 --> 04:59.324
(Sniffles) She was
a very spiritual person.

04:59.359 --> 05:00.792
She didn't have any enemies.

05:00.827 --> 05:03.061
A witness saw a tall,
dark-haired man

05:03.096 --> 05:05.597
leaving here
around 2:30 yesterday.

05:05.631 --> 05:07.899
Does that sound like
anyone your mother knows?

05:07.934 --> 05:10.202
When was the last time
you two talked?

05:10.236 --> 05:11.703
Around 1:00.

05:13.021 --> 05:15.255
She said she had
her last client of the day,

05:15.290 --> 05:18.825
and then she was gonna spend
the afternoon in meditation.

05:18.860 --> 05:20.994
Do you know
the client's name?

05:21.029 --> 05:22.929
No. It was a mother
and a daughter.

05:22.964 --> 05:24.965
Their names should be
in her book.

05:24.999 --> 05:27.968
Well, there was a notation
in her calendar

05:28.002 --> 05:30.771
at 3:00--
the initials "T.J."

05:31.778 --> 05:33.946
Does that mean anything
to you?

05:33.980 --> 05:36.448
No. I'm sorry
I can't be more helpful.

05:36.483 --> 05:39.418
Hey, I remember this case.

05:39.452 --> 05:41.186
A guy's wife goes missing,

05:41.221 --> 05:42.955
he seems genuinely distraught,

05:42.989 --> 05:44.890
and then the cops find out
he had a girlfriend

05:44.924 --> 05:47.092
and that his marriage
was on the rocks.
Yeah.

05:47.127 --> 05:49.061
Did your mother
help on that case?

05:49.129 --> 05:51.363
Yeah, she had a vision of him
at a local bar

05:51.398 --> 05:53.265
with this pretty blonde
named Amber,

05:53.300 --> 05:55.234
so she went to the police
with the information.

05:55.268 --> 05:57.836
That's when they started
looking at him as a suspect.

05:57.871 --> 06:00.005
And then what happened?
He went to prison.

06:00.040 --> 06:02.174
That case really
put my mom on the map.

06:02.208 --> 06:03.809
Did your mother continue

06:03.843 --> 06:07.078
offering the police help after that?
Yes, all over the country.

06:07.113 --> 06:09.248
My mother helped put away
over a dozen people

06:09.282 --> 06:11.917
in the last ten years.

06:11.952 --> 06:14.253
So here's the list of all
the people that Penny Marchand

06:14.287 --> 06:16.155
claims her mom
helped to convict.

06:16.189 --> 06:17.723
Let's see if any of them
are out of jail

06:17.747 --> 06:19.481
and still holding a grudge.
On it.

06:19.533 --> 06:21.434
Vivien's 1:00 Monday clients
are here.

06:21.469 --> 06:23.003
They say they got a good look

06:23.032 --> 06:24.633
at the dark-haired guy
who was in her office.

06:24.662 --> 06:26.562
Names are
Paula and Marina Casillas.

06:27.354 --> 06:29.755
"Casillas"?
That's a good name.

06:29.790 --> 06:31.190
Hard to possessive pluralize,
though.

06:32.397 --> 06:34.131
(Imitates Ricardo Montalban)
The Casillases' car

06:34.166 --> 06:35.700
has broken down,

06:35.734 --> 06:36.969
so they will be late
for the symphony.

06:36.987 --> 06:39.422
The casillas--s--
casillases-es...

06:40.573 --> 06:41.374
They're waiting for you
in the lounge.

06:41.389 --> 06:42.857
All right. Thanks.

06:44.836 --> 06:46.838
Usually, we're her
last clients on Monday,

06:46.872 --> 06:48.139
but when we left,

06:48.215 --> 06:50.049
there was a man there
waiting for Vivien.

06:50.083 --> 06:53.285
She seemed surprised to see him,
like he wasn't expected.

06:53.320 --> 06:55.387
Oh, and he seemed upset.
I could tell.

06:55.422 --> 06:58.457
Could you describe him?
He was wearing dark clothes.

06:58.492 --> 07:00.960
He had black hair,
going gray at the temples.

07:00.994 --> 07:03.562
Oh, and he had a scar
on his face.

07:03.597 --> 07:05.464
I think
she called him Alfred.

07:05.499 --> 07:07.166
Or was it Albert?

07:07.200 --> 07:09.835
Okay. Well, thank you, both.
You've been very helpful.

07:09.870 --> 07:11.709
How long had you
been going to see Vivien?

07:11.719 --> 07:13.143
Four months.

07:13.437 --> 07:15.838
My husband Emilio
passed away in April.

07:17.009 --> 07:19.243
We both miss him so much.

07:19.278 --> 07:20.662
So she was helping you
get closure.

07:20.899 --> 07:22.033
Yes.

07:22.063 --> 07:24.665
Even at our first session,
Vivien...

07:24.699 --> 07:28.268
Already knew so much
about my Emilio.

07:28.364 --> 07:29.365
Like what?

07:29.421 --> 07:31.989
Well, she knew
he made vitamins for a living.

07:32.024 --> 07:34.759
She knew
he loved arroz con pollo.

07:34.793 --> 07:37.361
She also knew
he was a workaholic.

07:37.396 --> 07:39.663
And that he even died
at the office.

07:39.698 --> 07:41.198
Vivien said
she thought daddy

07:41.233 --> 07:43.634
had something very important
to tell us.

07:43.668 --> 07:47.405
She was going to commune
with his spirit last night.

07:48.840 --> 07:51.675
Now we'll never know.

07:52.698 --> 07:55.000
You're not gonna believe this.

07:55.012 --> 07:58.848
Vivien's daughter is pretty sure
that "Albert" is Albert Moreno.

07:58.882 --> 08:00.293
Albert "The Blade" Moreno?

08:00.637 --> 08:02.571
Former muscle
for the Spolano crime family.

08:02.605 --> 08:05.440
So Vivien helped put him away.
Mnh-mnh. He's her client.

08:06.388 --> 08:08.085
Vivien told Albert
that if he if he invested in

08:08.218 --> 08:10.853
a New Jersey real estate deal,
true happiness would be his.

08:10.887 --> 08:13.489
The deal fell through a month
ago. He lost everything.

08:13.523 --> 08:16.826
Ouch. You give a guy
like that bad advice,

08:16.860 --> 08:19.328
he'll see to it you are
sleeping with the fishes.

08:19.362 --> 08:22.131
Or you get stabbed in the neck
wi an ice pick...

08:23.292 --> 08:25.961
And stuffed in a couch.

08:25.995 --> 08:29.497
